    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The Fire-Linked Mounting is a modification to two Fixed Hardpoints that allow primary weapons to synchronize their fire when the same type of primary weapon with no constitution requirement is installed. This modification installs a dedicated gunner station for the hardpoints.</p>\n<p>Â </p>\n<p>When you Fire one of the primary weapons from this dedicated gunner station, you can use a bonus action to attack with the other primary weapon in the same firing arc if it has not yet been Fired this round. You don't add the ship's ability modifier to the damage roll of the bonus attack, unless that modifier is negative. A weapon that has been activated using your bonus action in this way cannot be Fired this round.</p>",
